<br>
Basically stating that the story and the flow of plot is something we see in all cultures even when they never met.<br>
<br>
The stories of Moses and Luke Skywalker follow the heroes journey. The story of Neo and Simba follow the heroes journey. The story of Hercules and Paul Attredies (sp?) follows the same story arc.<br>
<br>
Just reviewing any ancient civilizations' stories of their mythological heroes, and you will find this arc. So whether they were Anglo, Asian or African, the hero always followed a similar story. <br>
<br>
Read <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>the masks of God</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by joseph campbell if you want to be enlightened.   <br>
